### Undergraduate tutoring 

Since the start of my PhD, I have been tutoring undergraduate modules offered at the School of Politics and International Relations. 
<br />
As part of my teaching responsibilities, I prepare and deliver 50-minute tutorial sessions in line with the module coordinator's instructions, I hold regular office hours, correspond with students and grade midterm essays as well as final exams. 

Academic term | Course | Details
-----|-------|--------
Spring 2021 | [Comparative Politcs](https://sisweb.ucd.ie/usis/!W_HU_MENU.P_PUBLISH?p_tag=MODULE&MODULE=POL20020) (POL20020)  | Second-year undergraduate course. Taught 4 tutorial groups of 15-20 students each. Module coordinator: [Dr Martijn Schoonvelde](http://mschoonvelde.com). 
Fall 2020 | [Theories and Concepts in International Relations](https://sisweb.ucd.ie/usis/!W_HU_MENU.P_PUBLISH?p_tag=MODULE&MODULE=INRL20040) (INRL20040) |  Second-year undergraduate course. Taught 4 tutorial groups of 15-20 students each. Module coordinator: [Dr Tobias Theiler](https://people.ucd.ie/tobias.theiler). 
Spring 2020 | [Comparative Politcs](https://sisweb.ucd.ie/usis/!W_HU_MENU.P_PUBLISH?p_tag=MODULE&MODULE=POL20020) (POL20020)  | Second-year undergraduate course. Taught 4 tutorial groups of 15-20 students each. Module coordinator: [Dr Martijn Schoonvelde](http://mschoonvelde.com). 
Fall 2019 | [Foundations Political Theory and International Relations](https://sisweb.ucd.ie/usis/!W_HU_MENU.P_PUBLISH?p_tag=MODULE&MODULE=INRL10010) (INRL10010)  | First-year undergraduate course. Taught 4 tutorial groups of 15-20 students each. Module coordinator: [Dr Graham Finlay](https://people.ucd.ie/graham.finlay). 

